ance\", \"score\": 0.9993883716748432, \"rank\": 0.0004659889128321148, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"L-R\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medalist\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2554}, {\"ngram\": \"An Se\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2560}, {\"ngram\": \"young\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medalist\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"a photo\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's singles badminton competitions\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP It is worth noting that Chinese badminton player He Bingjiao held a Team Spain Olympic pin in her hand when taking to the podium to collect her silver medal \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 a gesture in honor of her Spanish opponent Carolina Marin who was forced to abandon the women's singles competition due to an injury.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 3073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2803, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9389779085036627, \"rank\": 0.06268746690380159, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2966, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"score\": 0.8601045392019582, \"rank\": 0.1626353993189431, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/CFP\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2777}, {\"ngram\": \"a Team Spain Olympic pin\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2868}, {\"ngram\": \"her hand\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2880}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\":